
- AngularJS Supports form Validations.

- if any error raised in form automatically corresponding errors stored
  into "$error" object.

- "$error" is the predefined object in angularjs used to store the form
  related errors.


Syntax.

    "form_logical_name".
    "element_logical_name".
    $error.
    "type of error"

Ex_1: text validation

<form name="myForm">
    <label>Uname.</label>
    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">***Mininum 3 characters are required***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">****Maximum 6 characters allowed***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required">****Can't Left Blank***</div>
</form>


Ex_2: email validation
----------------------
<form name="myForm">
    <label>Email</label>
    <input type="email"
           name="uemail"
           required>

    <div ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.email">****Please enter the valid email****</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uemail.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</div>
</form>


Ex_3: number validation
-----------------------
<form name="myForm">

    <label>Phone.<label>
    <input type="text"
           name="uphone"
           ng-pattern="/^[0-9]{10,10}$/"
           required>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.required">***Can't Left Blank***</div>
    <div ng-if="myForm.uphone.$error.pattern">****Please enter the valid phone number***</div>
</form>


validations by using ngMessages Module:
---------------------------------------

    - ngMessages is the predefined module, used to handle the form validations.

    - by using ngMessages module we can overcome the data redundancy.


Step 1:
    download ngMessages module by using bower.

[ "angular-messages" key representing ngMessages module related key in bower]
[ "angular-messages.min.js" representing ngMessages module ]


step 2:
    add the ngMessages module dependency.


step 3:
    create the validation messages in external template by using
    ng-message directive



step 4:
    import the validations























